The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Title for Anand
New Delhi: World rapid chess champion Viswanathan Anand continued his demolition act winning the Sao Paulo rapid chess tournament with a whopping three-point margin. World No. 2 Anand defeated local stalwart Gilberto Milos in the tenth and final round to take his points tally to 8.5 out of a possible 10, according to information received here on Wednesday. This is Anands third straight tournament victory following a double triumph on the German soil, where he won the Dortmund Sparkassen chess meeting and the Mainz chess classic duel against Spaniard Alexei Shirov. GM Ivan Morovioc Fernandez of Chile finished second in the overall standings with 5.5 points while the third spot was taken by GM Rafael Leitao of Brazil (4.5). Former world champion Anatoly Karpov of Russia and Brazilian Giovanni Vescovi ended on 4 points each. (PTI)  Copyright 
